-- CTC Media’s CTC TV Audience Declines in Russia, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-08-02T20:09:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-02/ctc-media-s-ctc-tv-audience-declines-in-russia-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel saw its average daily share of Russian viewers aged 18
years and older fall in the week to July 29, according to TNS-
Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, fell to 5.2 percent in the
week to July 29 from 5.3 percent a week earlier, data researcher
TNS-Global said by e-mail today. CTC remained the seventh most-
watched TV channel in the country in the week to July 29, the
data show.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over was unchanged at 5.8 percent, the data show. CTC remained
in fifth place among viewers 4 years old and over, TNS-Global
said.  Russia’s NTV Television was the most watched in both
categories. Rossiya-1, Pervyi Kanal and TNT remained ahead of
CTC among viewers 4 years and older, unchanged from the previous
week, the data show.  Government-controlled Pervyi Kanal was the second-most
watched among viewers 18 and older, pushing Rossiya-1 to the
third rank. TNT TV remained in fourth while REN TV and Fifth
Channel retained their fifth and sixth ranks among viewers 18
years and older in the week to July 29, the data showed.  To contact the reporters on this story:
